						               													<description>A quiz game (600 questions) that requires, as the name suggests, knowledge of Germany's state Saxony-Anhalt.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take turns to roll 2 dice and move the number of fields by either one die or by both dice round the track. The player then tries to answer a question determined by the black die (results 1, 2 or 3).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the question is answered correctly the player receives chips, depending on the color of the field, he landed on. If the answer is wrong, a second player is given the question. A special field (the City of Magdeburg) gives the players the opportunity earning more chips. Everyone has to stay on Magdeburg till the last Player arrives getting each turn Questions with potential more points. Then the second part starts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when the first player comes the second time to Magdeburg (different track).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the player to collect the highest value of chips.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
